wiki.text:
'Intelligence' has been defined in many different ways including, but not
limited to, logic, abstract thought, understanding, self-awareness,
communication, learning, having emotional knowledge, retaining, planning, and
problem solving.

Intelligence is most widely studied in humans, but has also been observed in
animals and in plants. Artificial intelligence is the simulation of intelligence
in machines.

Within the discipline of psychology, various approaches to human intelligence
have been adopted. The psychometric approach is especially familiar to the
general public, as well as being the most researched and by far the most widely
used in practical settings.<ref name=APA1995> Article in Wikipedia: </ref>
